sql:
SELECT division_id, COUNT(office_id) AS "Office Count"
FROM postal_offices
GROUP BY division_id;

external_knowledge:
- "Top-ranked" implies the highest frequency of occurrence within the respective category (type, division, region, circle);
- "Postal offices" are facilities that provide mail services;
- "Type, division, region, circle" are hierarchical administrative divisions within the postal system.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT po.office_id) AS total_postal_offices
FROM postal_offices po
JOIN office_user ou ON po.office_id = ou.office_id;

external_knowledge:
- "Top 3 postal offices" refers to those with the highest number of users;
- "Top 3 regions" refers to those with the highest number of postal offices;
- "Busting with the most patrons" means having the highest user count;
- "House the most postal offices" means having the highest number of postal offices.

- 'Head Post Office' is rated 5;
- 'Sub Post Office' is rated 3;
- Other office types are rated 1.

sql:
SELECT AVG(num_offices_per_division) AS average_offices_per_division
FROM (
  SELECT COUNT(office_id) AS num_offices_per_division
  FROM postal_offices
  GROUP BY division_id
);
